() Tj T*
(Finding #1: [Critical] Tautological comparison in staking.spend: datum.mint_policy_id ==) Tj T*
(  datum.mint_policy_id) Tj T*
(  Detector: tautological-comparison) Tj T*
(  Module: staking) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/staking.ak:30) Tj T*
(Description: Handler staking.spend compares `datum.mint_policy_id == datum.mint_policy_id`) Tj T*
(    — this is always True and likely a copy-paste bug. The intended validation is) Tj T*
(    silently bypassed.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Replace one side of the comparison with the intended variable or) Tj T*
(    parameter.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #2: [High] Multiple quantity_of calls in staking.spend may allow double-counting) Tj T*
(  Detector: quantity-of-double-counting) Tj T*
(  Module: staking) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/staking.ak:30) Tj T*
(Description: Handler staking.spend calls `quantity_of` 5 times to check asset quantities.) Tj T*
(    Without verifying mutual exclusivity, an attacker may satisfy multiple checks with) Tj T*
(    overlapping assets.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Use `value.tokens` or `value.without_lovelace` for exact value matching) Tj T*
(    instead of multiple independent quantity_of checks.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #3: [High] Multiple quantity_of calls in staking.mint may allow double-counting) Tj T*
(  Detector: quantity-of-double-counting) Tj T*
(  Module: staking) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/staking.ak:144) Tj T*
(Description: Handler staking.mint calls `quantity_of` 7 times to check asset quantities.) Tj T*
