(Finding #4: [Medium] Time-sensitive datum but no validity_range check in staking.spend) Tj T*
(  Detector: missing-validity-range) Tj T*
(  Module: staking) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/staking.ak:30) Tj T*
(Description: Datum field\(s\) [staked_at] suggest time-sensitive logic but handler never) Tj T*
(    accesses transaction.validity_range.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Check validity_range against the time field\(s\) to enforce temporal) Tj T*
(    constraints.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #5: [Medium] Incomplete Value check via quantity_of in staking.mint) Tj T*
(  Detector: incomplete-value-extraction) Tj T*
(  Module: staking) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/staking.ak:144) Tj T*
(Description: Handler staking.mint uses quantity_of to check specific asset quantities but) Tj T*
(    doesn't validate the full Value. Other native assets may be drained.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Complement quantity_of checks with assets.match for full Value validation.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #6: [Medium] Withdrawal existence-only check in staking.spend) Tj T*
(  Detector: withdraw-amount-check) Tj T*
(  Module: staking) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/staking.ak:30) Tj T*
(Description: Handler staking.spend checks withdrawal existence but not the amount. An) Tj T*
(    attacker can invoke the staking script with a 0-amount withdrawal.) Tj T*
(  Recommendation: Verify the withdrawal amount is > 0 or matches an expected value.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
